'''Russell Hartley Adams''' (April 22, 1899 – March 19, 1956) was an American attorney who served as [[Allegheny County District Attorney]], including metropolitan [[Pittsburgh]], from January 1942 until December 17, 1945.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=jsJRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=v2kDAAAAIBAJ&dq=artemas%20leslie%20appoint&pg=4348,2011666|title=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette - Google News Archive Search|website=news.google.com|access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref> He was a member of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=YTAbAAAAIBAJ&sjid=kUwEAAAAIBAJ&dq=russell%20adams%20allegheny%20county%20district&pg=5333,15627|title=The Pittsburgh Press - Google News Archive Search|website=news.google.com|access-date=2017-09-14}}</ref>

Adams was born in [[Duquesne, Pennsylvania]], to Harry H. Adams and Gwendolyn Davis. He died of [[coronary occlusion]] in [[Mt. Lebanon, Pennsylvania]].<ref>''U.S. WWII Draft Cards Young Men, 1940-1947''</ref><ref>''Pennsylvania, Death Certificates, 1906-1966''</ref>

